Type Definitions

DidlBrowseItem

Transformed data of Browse action response.
Type:
  • Object
Properties:
Name Type Default Description
id string object id, can be used for Browse command
title string title
artist string '' artist
uri string '' AVTransportation URI
artUri string '' URI of cover, if available
metadata string '' metadata usually in DIDL Lite format
sid string '' music service id (derived from uri)
serviceName string '' music service name such as Amazon Music (derived from uri)
upnpClass string '' UPnP Class (derived from uri or upnp class)
processingType string '' can be 'queue', 'stream', 'unsupported' or empty (calculated)
Source:
  • Sonos-Commands.js, line 40

URL

URL components. Especially playerUrlOrigin is used for all sendToPlayer calls.
Type:
  • object
Properties:
Name Type Description
playerUrlHostname string such as 192.168.178.35
playerUrlPort string such as 1400
playerUrlHost string such as "192.168.178.35:1400"
playerUrlOrigin string such as "http://192.168.178.35:1400"
baseUrl string alias for playerUrlOrigin, will be replaced step by step
Source:
  • Sonos-Commands.js, line 28
